WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.123 --> 00:00:09.125
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:09.208 --> 00:00:12.003
♪ ♪

3
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:01:48.975 --> 00:01:50.410
Princess Rhaenys:
It's been near six years

5
00:01:50.434 --> 00:01:52.855
since I last saw
my lord husband. Maester.

6
00:01:53.605 --> 00:01:57.568
I must know... will he live?

7
00:01:57.651 --> 00:02:00.069
Maester Kelvyn:
He led his sailors into an ambush.

8
00:02:00.152 --> 00:02:04.241
A ship made to look
as if it were abandoned.

9
00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:08.744
In the fighting.
his neck was slashed by a corsair's dagger.

10
00:02:08.828 --> 00:02:11.373
He fell overboard into the sea.

11
00:02:11.456 --> 00:02:13.416
The wound was severe.

12
00:02:13.499 --> 00:02:15.127
Much blood was lost.

13
00:02:15.209 --> 00:02:18.088
But the greater concern
is the fever that followed.

14
00:02:18.171 --> 00:02:22.092
The ship's maester said
he burns from within.

15
00:02:24.093 --> 00:02:26.387
(seabirds calling)

16
00:02:34.521 --> 00:02:36.273
The ravens came in from?

17
00:02:36.355 --> 00:02:38.524
Kelvyn:
Evenfall. Princess.

18
00:02:39.318 --> 00:02:41.194
So they arrive in three days.

19
00:02:44.363 --> 00:02:46.444
Let all be made ready
to receive him. Maester Kelvyn.

20
00:02:53.665 --> 00:02:54.790
The Sea Snake is strong.

21
00:02:54.874 --> 00:02:56.542
Vaemond Velaryon:
No doubt.

22
00:02:56.627 --> 00:03:01.464
And yet. I have seen
blood fever overcome men half his age.

23
00:03:01.547 --> 00:03:04.676
I will not suffer the talk
of crows in my house. Vaemond.

24
00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:07.428
I love my brother...

25
00:03:07.511 --> 00:03:10.140
but we must be honest
with ourselves.

26
00:03:10.223 --> 00:03:12.308
We may greet his ship
to find him gone.

27
00:03:12.391 --> 00:03:14.977
And who will take
the Driftwood Throne?

28
00:03:15.062 --> 00:03:16.782
My grandmother seems
quite comfortable here.

29
00:03:16.855 --> 00:03:20.983
She presides
only in the absence of her husband.

30
00:03:21.068 --> 00:03:22.736
On his death. the seat passes.

31
00:03:22.819 --> 00:03:24.862
To Lucerys Velaryon.

32
00:03:24.946 --> 00:03:26.530
As is my lord husband's desire.

33
00:03:26.615 --> 00:03:29.992
I am the Sea Snake's own blood.

34
00:03:30.076 --> 00:03:32.703
the closest kin he has left.

35
00:03:32.788 --> 00:03:34.039
Be careful. good-brother.

36
00:03:34.122 --> 00:03:36.833
One could take
your words for treason.

37
00:03:45.717 --> 00:03:48.552
I speak the truth. Rhaenys.

38
00:03:49.720 --> 00:03:52.265
And you know it.

39
00:03:52.349 --> 00:03:54.016
The matter has been decided.

40
00:03:54.100 --> 00:03:55.243
Vaemond:
By a man whose ambition

41
00:03:55.267 --> 00:03:59.772
has brought down on us
calamity after calamity.

42
00:03:59.856 --> 00:04:03.068
My brother cares only
for the history books.

43
00:04:05.195 --> 00:04:07.488
But what of the Velaryon line?

44
00:04:07.571 --> 00:04:09.199
Is it to be snuffed out.

45
00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:13.202
supplanted by the pups
of House Strong?

46
00:04:13.285 --> 00:04:16.038
Driftmark is mine by all rights.

47
00:04:16.122 --> 00:04:18.833
And while I should
like your support.

48
00:04:18.917 --> 00:04:22.004
I do not... need it.

49
00:04:24.213 --> 00:04:27.050
The winds have shifted.

50
00:04:27.134 --> 00:04:31.388
The crown has good reason...
to take my side.

51
00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:34.348
My cousin the King would
have your tongue for this.

52
00:04:34.432 --> 00:04:39.228
But it's not a king who sits
the Iron Throne these days. good-sister.

53
00:04:40.271 --> 00:04:41.857
It's a queen.

54
00:04:43.984 --> 00:04:47.862
(tense music playing)

55
00:04:51.033 --> 00:04:53.117
(wind whistling)

56
00:05:15.223 --> 00:05:17.266
♪ ♪

57
00:05:19.811 --> 00:05:21.646
(footsteps approaching)

58
00:05:29.821 --> 00:05:32.865
♪ ♪

59
00:05:44.543 --> 00:05:47.338
♪ ♪

60
00:05:57.807 --> 00:06:01.602
(hissing)

61
00:06:08.485 --> 00:06:10.528
♪ ♪

62
00:06:23.374 --> 00:06:25.585
(speaking High Valyrian)

63
00:06:44.396 --> 00:06:45.437
♪ ♪

64
00:06:58.160 --> 00:07:00.244
(indistinct chatter)

65
00:07:00.328 --> 00:07:01.037
Prince Jacaerys:
The Conqueror and his sisters

66
00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.040
sailed with a great army.

67
00:07:04.124 --> 00:07:06.268
Maester Gerardys:
(speaking High Valyrian) Se Blakuata Rasho

68
00:07:06.292 --> 00:07:09.336
dranot vilinio viartis.

69
00:07:09.420 --> 00:07:13.550
Jacaerys:
(exhales) And landed at the Blackwater Rush.

70
00:07:13.633 --> 00:07:14.675
Dranot.

71
00:07:15.968 --> 00:07:18.513
Jacaerys:
Dranot. Dranot.

72
00:07:18.596 --> 00:07:20.639
Dranot. At the end?

73
00:07:20.723 --> 00:07:25.269
- The mouth.
- Mouth! Ah. come on. Jace. you knew that.

74
00:07:25.978 --> 00:07:28.564
Dranot. Dranot.

75
00:07:28.648 --> 00:07:31.817
- Dranot vilinio viartis.
- Dranot.

76
00:07:32.569 --> 00:07:34.862
Dranot.
Come on. Jace.

77
00:07:34.946 --> 00:07:36.465
Perhaps that's enough
for this morning.

78
00:07:36.489 --> 00:07:38.490
No. no.
I-I want to keep going.

79
00:07:39.951 --> 00:07:43.580
- Maester.
- Guesi misenakson Aegon undas.

80
00:07:43.663 --> 00:07:48.877
Aegon... ordered
that the trees should be...

81
00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:49.978
- ...killed.
- Princess Rhaenyra: Felled.

82
00:07:50.002 --> 00:07:51.879
It is a related word.

83
00:07:51.963 --> 00:07:55.383
I don't expect you
to learn High Valyrian in a day. Jace.

84
00:07:55.466 --> 00:07:58.761
A king should honor
the traditions of his forbears.

85
00:07:58.845 --> 00:08:01.139
Well...
unless you're planning

86
00:08:01.223 --> 00:08:02.682
to depose your own mother.

87
00:08:02.766 --> 00:08:05.018
you have plenty
of time to study.

88
00:08:05.100 --> 00:08:07.896
(door opens)

89
00:08:12.816 --> 00:08:13.860
Leave us.

90
00:08:15.028 --> 00:08:17.655
Joffrey... come.

91
00:08:38.552 --> 00:08:41.845
He means to call
into question Luke's legitimacy.

92
00:08:42.681 --> 00:08:43.681
And by extension Jace.

93
00:08:43.722 --> 00:08:46.685
and by extension
my own claim to the throne.

94
00:08:46.768 --> 00:08:48.728
Vaemond cares only
about Driftmark

95
00:08:48.812 --> 00:08:50.938
and the Velaryon line.

96
00:08:51.022 --> 00:08:53.358
Not about our politics.

97
00:08:53.441 --> 00:08:55.485
Has he made common cause
with Otto Hightower yet?

98
00:08:55.567 --> 00:08:57.320
Hm. this is what I fear.

99
00:08:57.403 --> 00:08:58.654
Rhaenys has flown to court.

100
00:08:58.738 --> 00:09:01.865
Surely. she cannot be planning to back him.
- No.

101
00:09:01.950 --> 00:09:03.219
Whatever disagreements
we may have had.

102
00:09:03.243 --> 00:09:04.494
she's not cruel...

103
00:09:04.576 --> 00:09:08.206
- or stupid enough to do that.
- Disagreements?

104
00:09:08.289 --> 00:09:11.375
She believes
we had her son killed so that we might marry.

105
00:09:11.459 --> 00:09:15.171
Yes... and yet.
she's taken Baela to ward.

106
00:09:15.254 --> 00:09:18.008
Yes. It is Laena's
memory she honors. She has no love for us.

107
00:09:19.801 --> 00:09:22.095
Has the vipers' venom
spread so far?

108
00:09:22.177 --> 00:09:25.222
Those vipers rule
in my father's name.

109
00:09:25.307 --> 00:09:26.932
And my father...

110
00:09:29.436 --> 00:09:32.480
(sighs)

111
00:09:33.940 --> 00:09:35.816
What choice do I have?

112
00:09:36.735 --> 00:09:38.528
(Rhaenyra sighs)

113
00:09:42.115 --> 00:09:43.950
To King's Landing. then.

114
00:09:47.119 --> 00:09:50.206
(intense music playing)

115
00:09:50.289 --> 00:09:52.334
(birds cawing)

116
00:10:02.427 --> 00:10:05.471
♪ ♪

117
00:10:24.658 --> 00:10:27.744
Steffon Darklyn:
All hail Rhaenyra of House Targaryen.

118
00:10:27.826 --> 00:10:29.680
Princess of Dragonstone
and heir to the Iron Throne

119
00:10:29.703 --> 00:10:34.084
and her royal consort.
Prince Daemon Targaryen.

120
00:10:34.167 --> 00:10:36.211
(bells tolling)

121
00:11:07.991 --> 00:11:10.077
Welcome back. Princess.

122
00:11:10.577 --> 00:11:12.205
Lord Caswell.

123
00:11:21.797 --> 00:11:23.090
I would say it's
nice to be home.

124
00:11:23.173 --> 00:11:26.427
- but I scarcely recognize it.
- Prince Daemon: Mm.

125
00:11:30.597 --> 00:11:35.854
Lyman Beesbury:
We have continued to enjoy improved customs duties

126
00:11:35.937 --> 00:11:38.313
since the settling
of the Stepstones.

127
00:11:38.398 --> 00:11:41.401
And the extent to
which we exploit those

128
00:11:41.484 --> 00:11:45.696
is contingent on
the harbor master's receipts.

129
00:11:45.779 --> 00:11:50.869
Of which. um. uh.
the. uh. septons have requested

130
00:11:50.951 --> 00:11:53.328
half that again
for a bronze bust

131
00:11:53.413 --> 00:11:54.746
they wish to co... to commission

132
00:11:54.831 --> 00:11:57.082
for the. the Festival
of the Mother.

133
00:11:57.167 --> 00:11:58.585
which I would not recommend.

134
00:11:58.667 --> 00:12:01.462
Thank you for that exhaustive
accounting. Lord Beesbury.

135
00:12:01.546 --> 00:12:04.590
I remind you...

136
00:12:10.345 --> 00:12:12.432
Your guests have arrived.
Your Grace.

137
00:12:12.514 --> 00:12:14.409
I trust they've been welcomed
as befits their station.

138
00:12:14.433 --> 00:12:17.353
As you instructed. Lord Hand.

139
00:12:18.937 --> 00:12:20.416
Grand Maester Orwyle:
It was my understanding Lord Corlys wished

140
00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:22.734
for his grandson Lucerys

141
00:12:22.816 --> 00:12:24.693
to succeed him
as Lord of the Tides.

142
00:12:24.777 --> 00:12:27.864
The boy has been raised
most of his life away from Driftmark.

143
00:12:27.946 --> 00:12:32.159
He can fly a dragon. yes.
but can he command a fleet?

144
00:12:32.243 --> 00:12:34.620
Ability does not
alter his claim.

145
00:12:34.703 --> 00:12:37.581
The Sea Snake has never
formally named him as heir.

146
00:12:37.664 --> 00:12:39.042
if it comes to that.

147
00:12:39.124 --> 00:12:41.711
The crown must choose
what is best for the realm.

148
00:12:41.793 --> 00:12:44.379
He is Laenor's son.
What grounds could there be...

149
00:12:44.464 --> 00:12:46.590
What indeed. Lord Beesbury.

150
00:12:46.673 --> 00:12:49.302
What indeed.

151
00:12:49.384 --> 00:12:50.571
We shall hear
Princess Rhaenyra's petition.

152
00:12:50.595 --> 00:12:52.971
along with those
of the other claimants on the morrow.

153
00:12:53.056 --> 00:12:56.058
- But...
- I do beg your pardon. my lords.

154
00:12:56.142 --> 00:12:57.560
I must greet our guests.

155
00:13:02.898 --> 00:13:05.777
Shall we levy a tax
on the sale of new wool?

156
00:13:05.860 --> 00:13:06.778
Your Grace...

157
00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:09.656
a matter has arisen that
requires your attention.

158
00:13:09.739 --> 00:13:11.865
Whatever it is. Ser Arryk.
it'll need to wait.

159
00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:15.744
- I'm Erryk. Your Grace.
- Of course. My apologies. ser.

160
00:13:15.827 --> 00:13:17.496
It's about the Prince.

161
00:13:17.580 --> 00:13:20.582
There's been
a delicate situation in his apartments.

162
00:13:24.044 --> 00:13:26.922
(unsettling music playing)

163
00:13:52.115 --> 00:13:53.991
- Father?
- (wheezing breaths)

164
00:13:55.201 --> 00:13:58.996
♪ ♪

165
00:14:01.791 --> 00:14:02.959
(wheezing)

166
00:14:09.382 --> 00:14:12.259
(melancholy music playing)

167
00:14:17.889 --> 00:14:21.603
- Who goes there?
- Rhaenyra: Father.

168
00:14:22.812 --> 00:14:25.440
It's me. my King.

169
00:14:26.231 --> 00:14:29.277
Rhaenyra.

170
00:14:29.610 --> 00:14:30.903
King Viserys:
Oh...

171
00:14:31.278 --> 00:14:33.405
Oh.

172
00:14:35.825 --> 00:14:38.244
I'm here with Daemon.

173
00:14:38.327 --> 00:14:39.912
(exhales) Daemon?

174
00:14:40.580 --> 00:14:41.496
Daemon?

175
00:14:41.581 --> 00:14:45.710
(exhales) Daemon.

176
00:14:46.376 --> 00:14:47.919
(Viserys wheezes)

177
00:14:49.047 --> 00:14:50.340
Help me up.

178
00:14:52.133 --> 00:14:53.717
(groaning)

179
00:14:56.678 --> 00:14:58.764
Oh...

180
00:14:58.847 --> 00:14:59.932
(labored breathing)

181
00:15:06.022 --> 00:15:07.481
(exhales)

182
00:15:07.565 --> 00:15:08.899
It has been so long.

183
00:15:14.446 --> 00:15:19.243
The Sea Snake has taken
a grave wound in battle in the Stepstones.

184
00:15:20.702 --> 00:15:21.537
When?

185
00:15:21.620 --> 00:15:24.081
We won that war years ago.

186
00:15:24.164 --> 00:15:25.957
No.

187
00:15:27.460 --> 00:15:29.336
The Triarchy is resurgent.

188
00:15:30.587 --> 00:15:32.382
The fighting is anew.

189
00:15:32.465 --> 00:15:37.220
And there is a p...
There is a petition to decide upon the succession of Driftmark

190
00:15:37.302 --> 00:15:39.346
and the heir
to the Driftwood Throne.

191
00:15:40.139 --> 00:15:41.307
(Viserys sighs)

192
00:15:42.225 --> 00:15:44.143
Viserys: Petitions?

193
00:15:45.978 --> 00:15:50.233
Alicent and Otto...
they see to all that business now.

194
00:15:50.316 --> 00:15:53.068
No. brother. listen to me.

195
00:15:53.152 --> 00:15:56.571
You are to affirm
your position for Lucerys

196
00:15:56.655 --> 00:15:58.240
to be Corlys Velaryon's
successor.

197
00:15:58.324 --> 00:16:00.993
(door opens)

198
00:16:01.076 --> 00:16:04.205
Has something happened
to Lord Corlys?

199
00:16:04.288 --> 00:16:05.831
(baby babbling)

200
00:16:05.914 --> 00:16:07.749
Father...

201
00:16:07.834 --> 00:16:10.794
there's someone we wish
to introduce you to.

202
00:16:14.090 --> 00:16:15.924
(labored breathing)

203
00:16:18.344 --> 00:16:19.928
(babbling continues)

204
00:16:24.350 --> 00:16:25.600
(sighs)

205
00:16:28.395 --> 00:16:31.441
Daemon.

206
00:16:31.858 --> 00:16:34.443
- Brother.
- (baby babbles)

207
00:16:35.528 --> 00:16:37.154
Who is that?

208
00:16:39.157 --> 00:16:40.783
Rhaenyra: Father...

209
00:16:41.993 --> 00:16:44.578
this is Aegon.

210
00:16:45.078 --> 00:16:46.621
Aegon. (exhales)

211
00:16:46.706 --> 00:16:50.585
And this... is Viserys.

212
00:16:51.668 --> 00:16:55.005
Ah... Viserys.

213
00:16:57.716 --> 00:16:59.177
Oh.

214
00:16:59.259 --> 00:17:03.765
(laughs)
Now that is a name fit for a king.

215
00:17:03.847 --> 00:17:05.432
(laughing)

216
00:17:07.727 --> 00:17:09.186
Oh...

217
00:17:11.521 --> 00:17:14.483
Oh. oh...

218
00:17:14.566 --> 00:17:15.817
Oh. I'm sorry.

219
00:17:16.568 --> 00:17:19.654
Oh. I'm sorry. I-I'm sorry.

220
00:17:19.739 --> 00:17:22.700
- (children crying)
- I'm so...

221
00:17:24.911 --> 00:17:27.704
Oh. I'm sorry. I'm sor...

222
00:17:27.788 --> 00:17:28.998
Please.

223
00:17:29.080 --> 00:17:30.333
(mouthing)

224
00:17:30.415 --> 00:17:34.002
- My tea... My tea.
- What tea? This?

225
00:17:34.086 --> 00:17:36.506
Yes. Yes.

226
00:17:37.923 --> 00:17:39.091
Yes.

227
00:17:41.051 --> 00:17:42.135
(children crying)

228
00:17:45.932 --> 00:17:47.599
(groans)

229
00:17:47.682 --> 00:17:50.519
(breathing heavily)

230
00:17:57.276 --> 00:18:00.028
(Viserys sighs)

231
00:18:00.112 --> 00:18:01.154
(servant crying)

232
00:18:06.911 --> 00:18:10.413
Talya:
I brought her here immediately.

233
00:18:10.498 --> 00:18:12.415
She's seen no one else.
Your Grace.

234
00:18:17.462 --> 00:18:19.339
- Come here. sweetling.
- (crying)

235
00:18:20.173 --> 00:18:21.759
(door closes)

236
00:18:28.891 --> 00:18:30.142
Tell me your name.

237
00:18:33.688 --> 00:18:39.067
It's Dyana. Your Grace.
If... i-if it please you.

238
00:18:40.944 --> 00:18:44.073
Dyana.
What a pretty name.

239
00:18:47.159 --> 00:18:49.161
I understand you've found
yourself in some trouble.

240
00:18:51.998 --> 00:18:54.709
I was fetching
the Prince his wine.

241
00:18:54.791 --> 00:18:58.753
and I put it on his table.
and when I turned...

242
00:18:59.337 --> 00:19:01.172
I didn't see him.

243
00:19:02.216 --> 00:19:03.593
I asked him to stop. Your Grace.

244
00:19:03.675 --> 00:19:07.345
I did. truly...

245
00:19:07.430 --> 00:19:09.432
you must believe me.

246
00:19:09.515 --> 00:19:12.559
(crying breaths)

247
00:19:18.065 --> 00:19:19.608
Shh.

248
00:19:23.320 --> 00:19:25.197
Thank you for telling me. Dyana.

249
00:19:30.493 --> 00:19:32.704
- I know it wasn't your fault.
- Hm?

250
00:19:34.874 --> 00:19:36.666
I believe you.

251
00:19:36.750 --> 00:19:38.336
Y-You do?

252
00:19:39.545 --> 00:19:40.796
I do.

253
00:19:43.798 --> 00:19:45.926
But what I worry about...

254
00:19:47.010 --> 00:19:48.171
is what others might believe.

255
00:19:50.221 --> 00:19:53.517
You were alone with the Prince.
were you not?

256
00:19:53.601 --> 00:19:55.769
Yes. I... (stammers)

257
00:19:55.853 --> 00:19:59.440
And no one else
saw what happened between the two of you.

258
00:19:59.522 --> 00:20:01.651
If anyone else were
to hear about this...

259
00:20:01.733 --> 00:20:06.822
- I haven't told anyone.
- You told Ser Erryk and Talya and now me.

260
00:20:06.905 --> 00:20:08.216
And though I believe
you are not to blame.

261
00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:11.618
others might not be so trusting.

262
00:20:11.701 --> 00:20:15.664
They might think you
were trying to besmirch the Prince. or worse...

263
00:20:15.748 --> 00:20:18.748
that you're the sort of girl
that might have enticed him in the first place.

264
00:20:20.294 --> 00:20:22.546
And you know what happens
to girls like that.

265
00:20:24.632 --> 00:20:28.259
I. I wouldn't dream
of breathing another word to anyone. Your Grace.

266
00:20:30.179 --> 00:20:31.721
I. I swear it on my life.

267
00:20:31.806 --> 00:20:34.767
(shuddering breaths)

268
00:20:39.814 --> 00:20:41.440
I know you won't.

269
00:20:54.370 --> 00:20:55.871
For your troubles.

270
00:20:55.954 --> 00:20:59.709
(door opens. closes)

271
00:21:03.461 --> 00:21:05.297
The tea. Your Grace.

272
00:21:18.978 --> 00:21:21.146
It's best to be certain.

273
00:21:40.374 --> 00:21:41.459
(Dyana gulps)

274
00:21:48.007 --> 00:21:50.425
Queen Alicent:
Get up.

275
00:21:50.509 --> 00:21:52.135
(shouts) Aegon!

276
00:21:54.805 --> 00:21:56.097
(yells) Get up!

277
00:21:56.848 --> 00:22:00.643
(sighs) Mother?

278
00:22:01.644 --> 00:22:05.816
- What is it?
- "What is it? What is it?

279
00:22:05.900 --> 00:22:07.794
What is it?"
That's all you can say for yourself?

280
00:22:07.817 --> 00:22:10.070
Has something happened?

281
00:22:10.153 --> 00:22:12.781
- Dyana.
- Mm?

282
00:22:12.865 --> 00:22:15.076
Alicent:
The serving girl.

283
00:22:15.159 --> 00:22:18.245
- (exhales)
- Oh. for the gods' sake.

284
00:22:18.328 --> 00:22:20.682
The girl. Aegon.
The one you sent fleeing from your company.

285
00:22:20.705 --> 00:22:23.291
Prince Aegon: (stretching)
Oh. it was just harmless fun.

286
00:22:23.374 --> 00:22:26.961
She didn't need to go
and get upset about it.

287
00:22:27.046 --> 00:22:31.174
Think of the shame
on your wife. on me.

288
00:22:31.258 --> 00:22:33.635
How can you keep
carrying on like this.

289
00:22:33.719 --> 00:22:35.637
especially on a day like today?

290
00:22:35.720 --> 00:22:38.723
Why? What is it today?

291
00:22:43.729 --> 00:22:45.772
(sniffles)

292
00:22:52.070 --> 00:22:53.948
You are no son of mine.

293
00:22:58.993 --> 00:23:01.329
I did not ask for this.

294
00:23:01.413 --> 00:23:04.290
I've done everything
you've asked me to.

295
00:23:04.374 --> 00:23:06.501
and I try so...

296
00:23:06.585 --> 00:23:09.922
I try so hard.
but it will never be enough for you or father.

297
00:23:10.005 --> 00:23:12.173
(door opens)

298
00:23:12.258 --> 00:23:16.220
Have you seen Dyana?
She's supposed to dress the children.

299
00:23:23.477 --> 00:23:25.645
He looks like
a different person.

300
00:23:25.729 --> 00:23:30.151
I believe we should also
consult Maester Gerardys.

301
00:23:30.233 --> 00:23:33.028
Perhaps if he
could see the King. he'd suggest a different...

302
00:23:33.112 --> 00:23:35.114
Princess Rhaenyra.

303
00:23:35.197 --> 00:23:36.865
- And Prince Daemon.
- Daemon: Hm.

304
00:23:39.326 --> 00:23:42.663
It has been so long
since we were granted the joy of your presence.

305
00:23:45.583 --> 00:23:47.125
Indeed. Your Grace.

306
00:23:47.209 --> 00:23:50.546
Though not long enough
to merit a greeting upon our arrival.

307
00:23:50.628 --> 00:23:53.548
I'm sure the Queen
had pressing business. my love.

308
00:23:53.632 --> 00:23:56.969
What can either of us
know of ruling a kingdom?

309
00:23:57.051 --> 00:23:58.845
I do not rule. as you well know.

310
00:23:58.929 --> 00:24:01.557
My father and I are mere
stewards of the King's will and wisdom.

311
00:24:01.640 --> 00:24:04.684
Daemon:
And how exactly is that wisdom expressed...

312
00:24:05.018 --> 00:24:06.060
hm?

313
00:24:06.144 --> 00:24:09.105
In blinks and wheezes?

314
00:24:09.190 --> 00:24:10.875
I'd be surprised
if he could remember his own name.

315
00:24:10.900 --> 00:24:12.734
- Or if you could.
- King Viserys's condition

316
00:24:12.817 --> 00:24:15.320
has worsened since you saw him last.
- Hah.

317
00:24:15.403 --> 00:24:18.115
It subjects him
to considerable pain.

318
00:24:18.199 --> 00:24:20.659
On the advice of the maesters...
- Ah. the maesters.

319
00:24:20.742 --> 00:24:24.204
Of course.
It is they who keep him...

320
00:24:24.288 --> 00:24:25.455
addled on milk of the poppy

321
00:24:25.538 --> 00:24:28.083
while the Hightowers
warm his throne.

322
00:24:28.166 --> 00:24:30.085
Rhaenyra. if you would
see him without it.

323
00:24:30.169 --> 00:24:32.480
- almost blind with suffering.
- Oh. Alicent. I have no doubt

324
00:24:32.503 --> 00:24:35.716
it was... an act
of the purest mercy.

325
00:24:35.798 --> 00:24:38.219
but tell me.
for the King's suffering.

326
00:24:38.301 --> 00:24:39.636
did the maesters also prescribe

327
00:24:39.720 --> 00:24:41.430
the removal
of Targaryen heraldry

328
00:24:41.512 --> 00:24:45.183
and the installation
in its stead of various statues and stars?

329
00:24:45.267 --> 00:24:47.703
The emblems of the Seven
serve only to guide us on an uncertain path.

330
00:24:47.728 --> 00:24:51.440
To remind us of a higher authority.
- And on the morrow.

331
00:24:51.522 --> 00:24:56.028
which authority will sit
in judgment of my son's claim on his own inheritance?

332
00:24:56.111 --> 00:24:58.780
- That would be mine... and the Hand's.
- Daemon: Ah.

333
00:24:58.864 --> 00:25:00.824
But be assured.
the Father is just and commands me

334
00:25:00.865 --> 00:25:04.161
to forget the accusations
you have hurled in this room today.

335
00:25:08.414 --> 00:25:10.250
(swords clashing)

336
00:25:10.334 --> 00:25:13.878
- Smaller than I remember.
- It looks exactly the same.

337
00:25:13.962 --> 00:25:16.923
- Ah. Luke. come on.
- (knights. squires grunting)

338
00:25:26.517 --> 00:25:27.601
(indistinct chatter)

339
00:25:30.729 --> 00:25:33.649
See? I told you this
would still be here.

340
00:25:33.731 --> 00:25:36.902
And you thought
you could swing Criston's morningstar.

341
00:25:36.986 --> 00:25:38.903
And you almost took
your own head off.

342
00:25:44.535 --> 00:25:47.203
- What's your problem?
- Everyone's staring at us.

343
00:25:47.288 --> 00:25:48.329
Hyah!

344
00:25:50.582 --> 00:25:52.582
No one would question me
being heir to Driftmark...

345
00:25:54.169 --> 00:25:56.171
if...

346
00:25:56.255 --> 00:25:59.549
if I looked more like
Ser Laenor Velaryon than Ser Harwin Strong.

347
00:26:01.551 --> 00:26:03.970
It doesn't matter
what they think.

348
00:26:06.432 --> 00:26:09.351
- (crowd cheering)
- (distant grunting)

349
00:26:15.732 --> 00:26:17.317
(grunting)

350
00:26:18.609 --> 00:26:20.112
- (crowd gasps)
- Ooh.

351
00:26:28.953 --> 00:26:31.999
(sword whooshes)

352
00:26:34.792 --> 00:26:36.377
(yelling)

353
00:26:42.300 --> 00:26:43.719
(crowd applauds)

354
00:26:48.766 --> 00:26:50.351
Well done. my Prince.

355
00:26:50.433 --> 00:26:51.786
You'll be winning
tourneys in no time.

356
00:26:51.809 --> 00:26:53.979
I don't give a shit
about tourneys.

357
00:26:54.813 --> 00:26:55.855
Nephews...

358
00:26:57.316 --> 00:26:59.567
have you come to train?

359
00:26:59.651 --> 00:27:01.028
Guard: (shouts)
Open the gate!

360
00:27:01.111 --> 00:27:03.154
(gate opening)

361
00:27:12.498 --> 00:27:15.459
(intense music playing)

362
00:27:15.541 --> 00:27:16.626
(footsteps marching)

363
00:27:35.062 --> 00:27:36.771
Otto Hightower:
Hold your nerve. my Queen.

364
00:27:36.855 --> 00:27:39.400
What we do.
we do for the good of the realm.

365
00:27:39.482 --> 00:27:44.195
I must confess
a certain uneasiness now this is at hand.

366
00:27:44.278 --> 00:27:48.534
- He may yet live.
- But we must be prepared if he does not.

367
00:27:56.874 --> 00:27:58.794
The realm has enjoyed
a long peace.

368
00:27:58.876 --> 00:28:01.797
a credit to the work
of both Jaehaerys and Viserys.

369
00:28:01.880 --> 00:28:06.468
but the threat of war looms
and may arrive on our shores.

370
00:28:06.551 --> 00:28:09.512
When it does.
will you want a child at the command

371
00:28:09.595 --> 00:28:11.807
of the greatest fleet
in Westeros?

372
00:28:13.642 --> 00:28:14.726
We must. of course...

373
00:28:16.603 --> 00:28:18.814
act in the interest
of our subjects.

374
00:28:20.899 --> 00:28:24.528
The next Lord of the Tides
will be deeply in your debt. Your Grace.

375
00:28:25.278 --> 00:28:26.779
As will Driftmark...

376
00:28:26.864 --> 00:28:28.906
in all its strength.

377
00:28:29.407 --> 00:28:31.701
(bell tolling)

378
00:28:36.080 --> 00:28:37.708
(thundering)

379
00:28:46.383 --> 00:28:47.759
Rhaena Targaryen:
Grandmother?

380
00:28:51.596 --> 00:28:54.599
Rhaena.

381
00:29:00.439 --> 00:29:01.815
Baela said you might be here.

382
00:29:03.650 --> 00:29:06.153
She's done well as your ward.

383
00:29:06.236 --> 00:29:07.528
You've. um...

384
00:29:08.905 --> 00:29:09.364
raised her admirably.

385
00:29:09.448 --> 00:29:13.701
You honor me. Princess.

386
00:29:13.785 --> 00:29:16.538
Might I speak to the Princess
alone. Rhaena?

387
00:29:19.874 --> 00:29:20.918
Princess.

388
00:29:30.719 --> 00:29:32.554
I wondered for many an hour

389
00:29:32.637 --> 00:29:36.266
what your purpose
was in coming here.

390
00:29:36.349 --> 00:29:39.393
Whether you'd speak
for or against the suit brought by Ser Vaemond.

391
00:29:39.478 --> 00:29:42.314
But then. I realized...

392
00:29:42.396 --> 00:29:44.316
you intend to advocate
for yourself.

393
00:29:47.653 --> 00:29:50.239
This is no fair proceeding.

394
00:29:50.322 --> 00:29:52.406
It is a trap

395
00:29:52.490 --> 00:29:54.409
set by the Queen and the Hand.
I'd wager.

396
00:29:54.492 --> 00:29:56.286
to proclaim my son illegitimate.

397
00:29:56.370 --> 00:29:59.330
Yet you did worse
than that with Laenor.

398
00:30:01.333 --> 00:30:02.668
Did you not?

399
00:30:09.007 --> 00:30:10.675
I loved your son.

400
00:30:12.970 --> 00:30:15.931
You may not believe it
to be true. but I did.

401
00:30:19.684 --> 00:30:21.811
I did not order his death.

402
00:30:24.314 --> 00:30:27.276
Nor was I complicit in it.
I swear this to you.

403
00:30:34.700 --> 00:30:36.159
I'll make you an offer.

404
00:30:39.704 --> 00:30:40.830
Back Luke's claim.

405
00:30:40.913 --> 00:30:43.666
and let us betroth
Laena's children to mine.

406
00:30:45.711 --> 00:30:50.214
Baela will be Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms

407
00:30:50.298 --> 00:30:52.968
and her sons will be
heirs to the throne.

408
00:30:53.050 --> 00:30:55.136
Rhaena will rule
in Driftmark. and...

409
00:30:55.220 --> 00:30:58.390
the seat will pass
to her and Lucerys's children in time.

410
00:30:58.472 --> 00:31:00.976
A generous offer.

411
00:31:01.058 --> 00:31:02.978
(thunder rumbling)

412
00:31:03.060 --> 00:31:05.980
- Or a desperate one.
- What does it matter?

413
00:31:07.566 --> 00:31:09.651
(soft chuckle)

414
00:31:09.734 --> 00:31:12.613
You are right in this. at least.

415
00:31:16.866 --> 00:31:18.242
It does not matter.

416
00:31:25.083 --> 00:31:27.752
♪ ♪

417
00:31:27.836 --> 00:31:31.006
You can bargain
with me all you like.

418
00:31:31.088 --> 00:31:34.634
Bring my granddaughter
with you to soften my resolve.

419
00:31:36.135 --> 00:31:38.930
But tomorrow.
the Hightowers land their first blow.

420
00:31:41.349 --> 00:31:43.434
They force you to your knees...

421
00:31:43.518 --> 00:31:46.355
and I must stand alone.

422
00:31:48.022 --> 00:31:50.858
(tense music playing)

423
00:32:00.076 --> 00:32:01.662
(exhales)

424
00:32:04.623 --> 00:32:07.875
(thundering. rain falling)

425
00:32:10.336 --> 00:32:12.047
(lightning cracks)

426
00:32:15.884 --> 00:32:18.010
(Viserys breathing heavily)

427
00:32:29.730 --> 00:32:31.816
(softly) Alicent?

428
00:32:32.483 --> 00:32:34.068
Alicent...

429
00:32:34.152 --> 00:32:36.113
No. it's Rhaenyra. father.

430
00:32:36.738 --> 00:32:39.324
(breathing heavily)

431
00:32:40.366 --> 00:32:42.326
Rhaenyra.

432
00:32:42.411 --> 00:32:44.371
(muttering)

433
00:32:44.453 --> 00:32:46.580
(thunder rumbling)

434
00:32:48.124 --> 00:32:51.377
"The Song of Ice and Fire."
Do you believe it to be true?

435
00:32:54.172 --> 00:32:55.966
Aegon's Dream.

436
00:32:59.970 --> 00:33:01.555
You told me

437
00:33:01.637 --> 00:33:05.642
it was our duty to hold
the realm united against a common foe.

438
00:33:09.813 --> 00:33:12.732
By naming me heir.
you divided the realm.

439
00:33:16.444 --> 00:33:19.322
(Viserys breathing heavily)

440
00:33:22.867 --> 00:33:23.951
I thought I wanted it.

441
00:33:34.880 --> 00:33:37.007
But the burden is a heavy one.

442
00:33:38.759 --> 00:33:41.635
(softly)
It's too heavy.

443
00:33:49.268 --> 00:33:50.353
My...

444
00:33:51.938 --> 00:33:53.105
My only child.

445
00:33:58.319 --> 00:34:01.280
If you wish me to bear it.
then defend me.

446
00:34:02.782 --> 00:34:04.326
And my children.

447
00:34:04.409 --> 00:34:05.701
(sighs)

448
00:34:08.245 --> 00:34:11.290
(quietly) It's...

449
00:34:13.084 --> 00:34:15.669
(thundering)

450
00:34:19.549 --> 00:34:22.051
(Viserys murmurs)

451
00:34:27.848 --> 00:34:29.935
(Rhaenyra sniffles)

452
00:34:30.643 --> 00:34:32.229
(crying)

453
00:34:35.941 --> 00:34:37.024
(bells tolling)

454
00:34:39.528 --> 00:34:42.321
(birds chirping)

455
00:34:44.281 --> 00:34:46.118
(breathing heavily)

456
00:35:05.846 --> 00:35:07.263
I want to have supper. Otto.

457
00:35:10.808 --> 00:35:14.270
- It is the morning. Your Grace.
- Tonight.

458
00:35:17.232 --> 00:35:19.901
The whole of my family...

459
00:35:19.984 --> 00:35:21.145
are gathered at the Red Keep.

460
00:35:24.488 --> 00:35:27.993
I want us... to dine together.

461
00:35:32.247 --> 00:35:33.790
(groaning)

462
00:35:40.129 --> 00:35:43.174
(groaning)

463
00:35:46.720 --> 00:35:50.098
(groaning continues)

464
00:35:58.899 --> 00:36:00.984
Bring milk of the poppy.

465
00:36:02.819 --> 00:36:04.904
(breathing heavily)

466
00:36:15.332 --> 00:36:16.415
(quietly) No.

467
00:36:18.792 --> 00:36:21.546
Just arrange the supper.

468
00:36:24.674 --> 00:36:26.801
(indistinct chatter)

469
00:36:26.884 --> 00:36:28.720
Though it is the great
hope of this court

470
00:36:28.803 --> 00:36:33.140
that Lord Corlys Velaryon
survive his wounds.

471
00:36:33.225 --> 00:36:35.643
we gather here
with the grim task

472
00:36:35.727 --> 00:36:38.187
of dealing with
the succession of Driftmark.

473
00:36:39.439 --> 00:36:41.816
As Hand. I speak with
the King's voice on this

474
00:36:41.899 --> 00:36:44.234
and all other matters.

475
00:36:46.696 --> 00:36:48.615
The crown will now
hear the petitions.

476
00:36:49.866 --> 00:36:51.743
Ser Vaemond of House Velaryon.

477
00:36:59.959 --> 00:37:01.669
Vaemond: My Queen.

478
00:37:01.752 --> 00:37:03.796
My Lord Hand.

479
00:37:04.672 --> 00:37:06.383
The history of our noble houses

480
00:37:06.466 --> 00:37:08.051
extends beyond
the Seven Kingdoms

481
00:37:08.133 --> 00:37:10.303
to the days of Old Valyria.

482
00:37:10.386 --> 00:37:13.223
For as long
as House Targaryen has ruled the skies.

483
00:37:13.305 --> 00:37:15.892
House Velaryon
has ruled the seas.

484
00:37:15.975 --> 00:37:17.977
When the Doom fell on Valyria.

485
00:37:18.060 --> 00:37:20.604
our houses became
the last of their kind.

486
00:37:20.689 --> 00:37:22.082
Our forebearers
came to this new land.

487
00:37:22.107 --> 00:37:24.024
knowing that were they to fail.

488
00:37:24.109 --> 00:37:28.654
it would mean the end
to their bloodlines and their name.

489
00:37:28.738 --> 00:37:32.533
I have spent my entire life
on Driftmark defending my brother's seat.

490
00:37:32.616 --> 00:37:36.370
I am Lord Corlys's closest kin.
his own blood.

491
00:37:36.453 --> 00:37:40.500
The true. unimpeachable
blood of House Velaryon runs through my veins.

492
00:37:40.582 --> 00:37:44.546
As it does in my sons.
the offspring of Laenor Velaryon.

493
00:37:44.629 --> 00:37:47.381
If you cared so much
about your house's blood. Ser Vaemond.

494
00:37:47.464 --> 00:37:49.843
you would not be so bold as
to supplant its rightful heir.

495
00:37:49.926 --> 00:37:51.678
No. you only speak for yourself

496
00:37:51.761 --> 00:37:53.531
- and for your own ambition.
- You will have chance

497
00:37:53.555 --> 00:37:55.765
to make
your own petition. Princess Rhaenyra.

498
00:37:55.848 --> 00:37:58.435
Do Ser Vaemond
the courtesy of allowing his to be heard.

499
00:38:03.564 --> 00:38:07.067
What do you know
of Velaryon blood. Princess?

500
00:38:08.361 --> 00:38:11.406
I could cut my veins
and show it to you

501
00:38:11.488 --> 00:38:14.616
and you still
wouldn't recognize it.

502
00:38:14.700 --> 00:38:18.747
This is about the future
and survival of my house. not yours.

503
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:26.087
My Queen. my Lord Hand.

504
00:38:27.129 --> 00:38:31.551
This is a matter of blood.
not ambition.

505
00:38:31.633 --> 00:38:35.430
I place the continuation
of the survival of my house and my line above all.

506
00:38:35.513 --> 00:38:40.685
I humbly put myself before you
as my brother's successor...

507
00:38:40.768 --> 00:38:44.272
the Lord of Driftmark
and Lord of the Tides.

508
00:38:45.439 --> 00:38:47.067
Thank you. Ser Vaemond.

509
00:38:53.198 --> 00:38:56.993
Princess Rhaenyra.
you may now speak

510
00:38:57.076 --> 00:38:59.495
for your son. Lucerys Velaryon.

511
00:39:04.959 --> 00:39:07.629
If I am to grace this farce
with some answer.

512
00:39:07.712 --> 00:39:10.752
I will start by reminding
the court that nearly 20 years ago. in this very...

513
00:39:16.553 --> 00:39:19.598
King Viserys of House Targaryen.

514
00:39:19.682 --> 00:39:21.600
the First of His Name.

515
00:39:21.683 --> 00:39:24.770
King of the Andals.
and the Rhoynar.

516
00:39:24.854 --> 00:39:27.107
and the First Men.

517
00:39:27.189 --> 00:39:32.444
Lord of the Seven Kingdoms.
and Protector of the Realm.

518
00:39:32.529 --> 00:39:35.615
(dark. triumphant music playing)

519
00:39:35.698 --> 00:39:37.366
♪ ♪

520
00:39:50.629 --> 00:39:53.424
♪ ♪

521
00:40:33.797 --> 00:40:37.551
♪ ♪

522
00:40:49.397 --> 00:40:51.524
(breathing heavily)

523
00:40:51.607 --> 00:40:53.484
I will sit the throne today.

524
00:40:55.444 --> 00:40:56.779
Your Grace.

525
00:41:00.241 --> 00:41:02.201
(groaning)

526
00:41:03.995 --> 00:41:06.080
I will be fine.

527
00:41:06.163 --> 00:41:09.000
(breathing heavily)

528
00:41:14.504 --> 00:41:16.089
(crown clatters)

529
00:41:20.678 --> 00:41:22.471
I said I'm fine.

530
00:41:25.975 --> 00:41:27.100
- Ah...
- Come on.

531
00:41:27.935 --> 00:41:29.520
(groaning)

532
00:41:34.359 --> 00:41:36.819
- Steady.
- (Viserys groans)

533
00:41:37.861 --> 00:41:39.446
(groaning)

534
00:41:45.995 --> 00:41:49.040
♪ ♪

535
00:42:08.392 --> 00:42:09.477
(breathing heavily)

536
00:42:16.276 --> 00:42:22.698
I must... admit... my confusion.

537
00:42:24.283 --> 00:42:25.701
I do not understand

538
00:42:25.785 --> 00:42:30.163
why petitions are being heard
over a settled succession.

539
00:42:30.247 --> 00:42:33.459
The only one present...

540
00:42:33.542 --> 00:42:37.171
who might offer keener insight
into Lord Corlys's wishes

541
00:42:37.254 --> 00:42:39.924
is the Princess Rhaenys.

542
00:42:43.720 --> 00:42:45.346
Indeed. Your Grace.

543
00:42:59.234 --> 00:43:02.196
It was ever my husband's
will that Driftmark

544
00:43:02.279 --> 00:43:04.198
pass through Ser Laenor

545
00:43:04.281 --> 00:43:07.118
to his trueborn son...

546
00:43:07.951 --> 00:43:09.037
Lucerys Velaryon.

547
00:43:09.120 --> 00:43:12.749
His mind never changed.

548
00:43:12.832 --> 00:43:15.084
Nor did my support of him.

549
00:43:15.167 --> 00:43:18.421
As a matter of fact.
the Princess Rhaenyra has just informed me of her desire

550
00:43:18.504 --> 00:43:20.589
to marry her sons Jace and Luke

551
00:43:20.672 --> 00:43:25.386
to Lord Corlys's granddaughters.
Baela and Rhaena.

552
00:43:25.470 --> 00:43:29.390
A proposal to which
I heartily agree.

553
00:43:30.390 --> 00:43:34.020
Viserys:
Well... the matter is settled.

554
00:43:35.312 --> 00:43:36.605
Again.

555
00:43:37.899 --> 00:43:39.399
I hereby reaffirm

556
00:43:39.484 --> 00:43:42.278
Prince Lucerys of House Velaryon

557
00:43:42.361 --> 00:43:45.406
as heir to Driftmark.

558
00:43:45.490 --> 00:43:50.453
the Driftwood Throne.
and the next Lord of the Tides.

559
00:43:50.535 --> 00:43:51.578
(wheezing)

560
00:43:56.959 --> 00:43:58.502
You break law...

561
00:43:59.587 --> 00:44:01.421
and centuries of tradition

562
00:44:01.506 --> 00:44:03.633
to install your daughter
as heir.

563
00:44:05.676 --> 00:44:08.388
Yet you dare tell me...

564
00:44:08.471 --> 00:44:11.390
who deserves to inherit
the name Velaryon.

565
00:44:13.683 --> 00:44:16.062
No.

566
00:44:16.145 --> 00:44:18.397
I will not allow it.

567
00:44:19.022 --> 00:44:20.649
"Allow it"?

568
00:44:21.734 --> 00:44:23.903
Do not forget yourself. Vaemond.

569
00:44:27.740 --> 00:44:32.370
(shouts)
That is no true Velaryon.

570
00:44:32.453 --> 00:44:35.957
and certainly no nephew of mine.

571
00:44:36.040 --> 00:44:38.125
Go to your chambers.
You have said enough.

572
00:44:39.419 --> 00:44:42.879
Lucerys is
my true-born grandson.

573
00:44:43.881 --> 00:44:45.383
And you...

574
00:44:45.466 --> 00:44:46.633
are no more

575
00:44:46.716 --> 00:44:49.846
than the second son
of Driftmark.

576
00:44:49.928 --> 00:44:54.683
You... may run your house
as you see fit...

577
00:44:54.767 --> 00:44:58.729
but you will not decide
the future of mine.

578
00:45:00.605 --> 00:45:02.899
My house survived the Doom

579
00:45:02.984 --> 00:45:05.736
and a thousand
tribulations besides.

580
00:45:05.819 --> 00:45:07.654
And gods be damned...

581
00:45:08.948 --> 00:45:13.870
I will not see it ended
on the account of this...

582
00:45:16.205 --> 00:45:17.747
(softly) Say it.

583
00:45:28.301 --> 00:45:30.511
Her children...

584
00:45:30.595 --> 00:45:32.846
(shouts) are bastards!

585
00:45:35.308 --> 00:45:37.560
And she...

586
00:45:38.435 --> 00:45:39.479
is...

587
00:45:40.270 --> 00:45:41.689
a whore.

588
00:45:41.772 --> 00:45:43.232
(crowd gasping)

589
00:45:43.316 --> 00:45:45.401
(breathing heavily)

590
00:45:48.154 --> 00:45:49.196
I...

591
00:45:50.990 --> 00:45:53.158
will have your tongue for that.

592
00:45:53.241 --> 00:45:56.287
(all gasping)

593
00:46:00.249 --> 00:46:01.542
He can keep his tongue.

594
00:46:01.625 --> 00:46:05.004
- (shouts) Disarm him!
- No need.

595
00:46:07.547 --> 00:46:09.633
(Viserys groaning)

596
00:46:11.801 --> 00:46:14.888
- Alicent: Call the maesters!
- Father?

597
00:46:14.971 --> 00:46:17.767
- (groaning)
- Please. my love. You must take something for the pain.

598
00:46:18.642 --> 00:46:20.393
I will not cloud my mind.

599
00:46:20.477 --> 00:46:22.854
I must put things right.

600
00:46:24.272 --> 00:46:25.816
(groaning)

601
00:46:39.162 --> 00:46:41.999
(solemn music playing)

602
00:47:08.984 --> 00:47:13.613
The body will be ready
for its return to Driftmark on the morrow. my lady.

603
00:47:16.200 --> 00:47:20.287
You may wish to leave
the Silent Sisters to their work.

604
00:47:20.370 --> 00:47:22.832
It is ill luck to look
upon the face of death.

605
00:47:26.334 --> 00:47:30.922
The Stranger has visited me
more times than I can count. Grand Maester.

606
00:47:36.178 --> 00:47:38.723
I assure you...

607
00:47:38.805 --> 00:47:41.808
he cares little
whether my eyes are open or closed.

608
00:48:01.328 --> 00:48:05.124
♪ ♪

609
00:48:13.506 --> 00:48:16.343
(indistinct chatter)

610
00:48:32.817 --> 00:48:33.861
(door opens)

611
00:49:07.977 --> 00:49:11.399
How good it is...
to see you all tonight...

612
00:49:12.524 --> 00:49:13.817
together.

613
00:49:19.781 --> 00:49:23.743
- Prayer before we begin?
- Yes.

614
00:49:23.828 --> 00:49:26.205
May the Mother smile down
on this gathering with love.

615
00:49:26.287 --> 00:49:30.917
May the Smith mend
the bonds that have been broken for far too long.

616
00:49:31.000 --> 00:49:33.962
And to Vaemond Velaryon.
may the gods give him rest.

617
00:49:42.178 --> 00:49:46.015
This is an occasion
for celebration. it seems.

618
00:49:46.100 --> 00:49:48.560
My grandsons. Jace and Luke.

619
00:49:48.643 --> 00:49:51.939
will marry their cousins.
Baela and Rhaena.

620
00:49:52.022 --> 00:49:55.276
further strengthening the bond
between our houses.

621
00:49:55.359 --> 00:49:57.944
A toast to the young Princes...

622
00:49:58.028 --> 00:50:02.241
- and their betrothed.
- Hear. hear!

623
00:50:02.323 --> 00:50:05.785
Well done. Jace.
You'll finally get to lie with a woman.

624
00:50:05.870 --> 00:50:10.374
Let us toast as well
Prince Lucerys...

625
00:50:10.457 --> 00:50:13.294
the future Lord of the Tides.

626
00:50:13.377 --> 00:50:14.462
Hear. hear.

627
00:50:14.544 --> 00:50:16.171
You'll be great.

628
00:50:19.883 --> 00:50:24.221
You do know how the act
is done. I assume?

629
00:50:24.305 --> 00:50:25.430
At least in principle?

630
00:50:25.513 --> 00:50:26.932
Where to put your cock
and all that.

631
00:50:27.015 --> 00:50:28.392
Let it be. cousin.

632
00:50:28.475 --> 00:50:29.618
You can play the jester
if you wish.

633
00:50:29.642 --> 00:50:33.272
but hold your tongue before my betrothed.
- Mm-hm.

634
00:50:45.533 --> 00:50:47.912
(cutlery clatters)

635
00:50:48.745 --> 00:50:51.457
(breathing heavily)

636
00:50:53.750 --> 00:50:58.296
It both gladdens my heart

637
00:50:58.379 --> 00:51:02.509
and fills me with sorrow

638
00:51:02.593 --> 00:51:05.805
to see these faces
around the table.

639
00:51:06.930 --> 00:51:10.725
The faces most dear
to me in all the world...

640
00:51:12.185 --> 00:51:14.479
yet grown so distant
from each other...

641
00:51:15.064 --> 00:51:17.524
in the years past.

642
00:51:30.120 --> 00:51:31.412
(mask thuds)

643
00:51:40.506 --> 00:51:43.926
My own face...

644
00:51:44.008 --> 00:51:46.303
is no longer a handsome one...

645
00:51:49.055 --> 00:51:50.140
if indeed it ever was.

646
00:51:54.270 --> 00:51:56.312
But tonight...

647
00:51:56.397 --> 00:51:59.774
I wish you to see me...
as I am.

648
00:52:01.192 --> 00:52:02.778
Not just a king...

649
00:52:04.488 --> 00:52:07.366
but your father.

650
00:52:07.448 --> 00:52:08.658
Your brother.

651
00:52:09.325 --> 00:52:10.953
Your husband...

652
00:52:13.288 --> 00:52:14.915
and your grandsire.

653
00:52:15.915 --> 00:52:18.084
Who may not. it seems...

654
00:52:19.086 --> 00:52:20.962
walk for much longer among you.

655
00:52:21.046 --> 00:52:24.508
- (breathing heavily)
- (mask clanks)

656
00:52:26.801 --> 00:52:31.348
Let us no longer hold
ill feelings in our hearts.

657
00:52:32.640 --> 00:52:34.267
The crown cannot stand strong

658
00:52:34.350 --> 00:52:37.020
if the House of the Dragon
remains divided.

659
00:52:37.854 --> 00:52:40.774
But set aside your grievances.

660
00:52:44.153 --> 00:52:46.321
if not for the sake
of the crown...

661
00:52:47.406 --> 00:52:49.575
then for the sake
of this old man

662
00:52:50.158 --> 00:52:53.078
who loves you all

663
00:52:53.162 --> 00:52:54.747
so dearly.

664
00:53:00.877 --> 00:53:02.962
(breathing heavily)

665
00:53:03.504 --> 00:53:05.633
(mask clanking)

666
00:53:21.689 --> 00:53:24.776
I wish to raise my cup
to Her Grace. the Queen.

667
00:53:28.738 --> 00:53:31.158
I love my father.

668
00:53:31.241 --> 00:53:34.745
But I must admit
that no one has stood...

669
00:53:34.828 --> 00:53:37.413
more loyally by his side
than his good wife.

670
00:53:37.497 --> 00:53:40.459
(poignant music playing)

671
00:53:40.542 --> 00:53:42.419
She has tended to him with...

672
00:53:43.587 --> 00:53:45.631
unfailing devotion.

673
00:53:45.714 --> 00:53:48.258
love. and honor.

674
00:53:49.718 --> 00:53:52.178
And for that.
she has my gratitude...

675
00:53:54.098 --> 00:53:55.683
and my apology.

676
00:54:05.024 --> 00:54:07.903
Your graciousness
moves me deeply. Princess.

677
00:54:07.986 --> 00:54:10.029
♪ ♪

678
00:54:11.198 --> 00:54:13.075
We are both mothers...

679
00:54:15.493 --> 00:54:17.370
and we love our children.

680
00:54:20.790 --> 00:54:23.711
We have more in common
than we sometimes allow.

681
00:54:26.964 --> 00:54:30.426
I raise my cup to you...
and to your house.

682
00:54:35.513 --> 00:54:37.473
You will make a fine queen.

683
00:54:39.810 --> 00:54:43.814
♪ ♪

684
00:55:07.754 --> 00:55:09.631
(Prince Aegon clears throat)

685
00:55:13.509 --> 00:55:15.471
I. um...

686
00:55:15.553 --> 00:55:19.058
I regret the disappointment
you are soon to suffer.

687
00:55:19.140 --> 00:55:22.602
But if you ever wish to know
what it is to be well satisfied.

688
00:55:22.685 --> 00:55:24.729
all you have to do is ask.

689
00:55:25.439 --> 00:55:28.107
Jace.

690
00:55:28.192 --> 00:55:31.069
(Prince Jacaerys clears throat)

691
00:55:54.218 --> 00:55:59.180
To Prince Aegon and...
Prince Aemond.

692
00:55:59.263 --> 00:56:02.642
We have not seen
each other in years.

693
00:56:02.725 --> 00:56:05.479
but I have fond memories
of our shared youth.

694
00:56:07.897 --> 00:56:12.861
And as men. I hope we may
yet be friends and allies.

695
00:56:12.944 --> 00:56:15.488
To you and your family's
good health. dear uncles.

696
00:56:23.497 --> 00:56:24.747
To you as well.

697
00:56:31.504 --> 00:56:33.924
(softly)
Beware the beast beneath the boards.

698
00:56:34.006 --> 00:56:35.424
Well done. my boy.

699
00:56:35.508 --> 00:56:39.805
I would like to toast
to Baela and Rhaena.

700
00:56:39.888 --> 00:56:42.765
They'll be married soon.

701
00:56:42.850 --> 00:56:46.060
It isn't so bad.
Mostly he just ignores you...

702
00:56:47.104 --> 00:56:49.189
except sometimes
when he's drunk.

703
00:56:49.272 --> 00:56:50.857
(scattered laughter)

704
00:56:57.613 --> 00:57:00.993
- (whispers) Good.
- Let us have some music.

705
00:57:01.075 --> 00:57:04.037
(lively music playing)

706
00:57:04.120 --> 00:57:06.247
(indistinct chatter)

707
00:57:06.330 --> 00:57:07.540
Excuse me.

708
00:57:24.850 --> 00:57:26.435
(laughing)

709
00:57:36.694 --> 00:57:38.279
(laughing)

710
00:57:39.656 --> 00:57:41.241
(inaudible)

711
00:57:46.205 --> 00:57:48.457
(emotional music playing)

712
00:57:57.674 --> 00:58:00.468
♪ ♪

713
00:58:29.038 --> 00:58:31.875
(breathes heavily)

714
00:58:38.381 --> 00:58:41.884
- Alicent: Guards.
- (Viserys groaning)

715
00:58:49.017 --> 00:58:50.560
Please. sit down.

716
00:58:50.643 --> 00:58:51.687
♪ ♪

717
00:59:13.582 --> 00:59:14.625
(pig sizzling)

718
00:59:20.549 --> 00:59:22.133
(chuckles)

719
00:59:27.263 --> 00:59:28.973
(hits table. music stops)

720
00:59:29.473 --> 00:59:31.435
Final tribute.

721
00:59:34.312 --> 00:59:36.439
To the health of my nephews:

722
00:59:37.274 --> 00:59:38.984
Jace...

723
00:59:39.067 --> 00:59:41.153
Luke...

724
00:59:42.111 --> 00:59:43.404
and Joffrey.

725
00:59:44.823 --> 00:59:48.200
Each of them handsome. wise...

726
00:59:52.830 --> 00:59:55.250
hm...

727
00:59:55.334 --> 00:59:56.877
- strong.
- Aemond.

728
00:59:56.959 --> 00:59:58.044
Prince Aemond: Come...

729
00:59:59.671 --> 01:00:03.966
let us drain our cups
to these three...

730
01:00:04.051 --> 01:00:05.444
- Strong boys.
- I dare you to say that again.

731
01:00:05.468 --> 01:00:09.348
Why? 'Twas only a compliment.

732
01:00:09.430 --> 01:00:11.558
Do you not think
yourself Strong?

733
01:00:11.640 --> 01:00:13.768
- Rhaenyra: Jace!
- Alicent: That is enough!

734
01:00:15.562 --> 01:00:16.604
(grunts)

735
01:00:17.772 --> 01:00:18.857
(chuckles)

736
01:00:18.939 --> 01:00:20.024
(grunting)

737
01:00:20.107 --> 01:00:21.877
Why would you
say such a thing before these people?

738
01:00:21.901 --> 01:00:25.906
I was merely expressing
how proud I am of my family. Mother.

739
01:00:25.988 --> 01:00:29.868
Mm. though it seems
my nephews aren't quite as proud of theirs.

740
01:00:29.950 --> 01:00:31.787
Daemon: Wait. wait!

741
01:00:35.415 --> 01:00:37.667
Rhaenyra:
Go to your quarters. All of you go. now.

742
01:00:40.169 --> 01:00:41.421
(sighs)

743
01:00:42.171 --> 01:00:45.049
(footsteps retreating)

744
01:00:49.678 --> 01:00:52.682
Mm.

745
01:00:57.270 --> 01:01:00.314
Rhaenyra.

746
01:01:02.859 --> 01:01:05.529
It's best. I think. if we
go back to Dragonstone.

747
01:01:05.611 --> 01:01:06.696
You've only just arrived.

748
01:01:13.537 --> 01:01:14.703
Let me see the children home.

749
01:01:16.372 --> 01:01:17.707
I'll. um...

750
01:01:18.375 --> 01:01:20.919
return on dragonback.

751
01:01:25.381 --> 01:01:27.299
The King and I
would both like that.

752
01:01:40.564 --> 01:01:41.647
(indistinct chatter)

753
01:01:47.236 --> 01:01:50.073
(mysterious music playing)

754
01:01:51.408 --> 01:01:53.243
(dog barking)

755
01:02:00.292 --> 01:02:01.917
(chatter continues)

756
01:02:09.008 --> 01:02:12.261
It's been quite a night
at the castle. it seems.

757
01:02:13.555 --> 01:02:15.098
Yes. my lady.

758
01:02:18.560 --> 01:02:20.604
♪ ♪

759
01:02:32.948 --> 01:02:35.910
- (footsteps approach)
- (Viserys groaning)

760
01:02:49.924 --> 01:02:51.759
Come on. come on.

761
01:02:55.471 --> 01:02:57.890
- That's it.
- (breathing heavily)

762
01:03:00.810 --> 01:03:01.937
(groans)

763
01:03:06.982 --> 01:03:08.026
Oh...

764
01:03:09.361 --> 01:03:10.654
Well done.

765
01:03:17.493 --> 01:03:19.662
- I'm sorry.
- Shh.

766
01:03:19.745 --> 01:03:21.872
- I'm sorry.
- Shh. shh. shh.

767
01:03:24.375 --> 01:03:26.252
But you wanted to know...

768
01:03:27.337 --> 01:03:29.421
if I believe it to be true.

769
01:03:31.341 --> 01:03:33.218
Believe what to be true.
my King?

770
01:03:34.176 --> 01:03:35.803
Don't you remember?

771
01:03:37.555 --> 01:03:40.600
Aegon...

772
01:03:41.350 --> 01:03:44.395
Our son?

773
01:03:44.854 --> 01:03:46.939
His Dream.

774
01:03:47.022 --> 01:03:48.149
The Song of Ice...

775
01:03:48.232 --> 01:03:50.276
and Fi...

776
01:03:51.569 --> 01:03:53.154
It is true.

777
01:03:54.196 --> 01:03:56.073
What he saw in the North.

778
01:03:57.741 --> 01:03:59.868
The Prince That Was Promised.

779
01:04:01.745 --> 01:04:03.122
I don't understand. Viserys.

780
01:04:03.205 --> 01:04:05.292
(sighs)
The Prince.

781
01:04:05.375 --> 01:04:06.917
Prince Aegon?

782
01:04:09.129 --> 01:04:10.796
To unite the realm

783
01:04:10.879 --> 01:04:14.049
against the cold...
and the dark.

784
01:04:17.846 --> 01:04:19.430
It is you.

785
01:04:22.225 --> 01:04:25.270
You are the one.

786
01:04:25.770 --> 01:04:26.854
You must do this.

787
01:04:28.564 --> 01:04:31.442
(softly) You must do this.

788
01:04:32.944 --> 01:04:34.029
(breathing heavily)

789
01:04:51.629 --> 01:04:53.214
Shh. shh.

790
01:04:54.299 --> 01:04:56.759
(exhales deeply)

791
01:05:10.522 --> 01:05:12.901
(blows out candle)

792
01:05:16.071 --> 01:05:17.906
I understand. my King.

793
01:05:23.118 --> 01:05:24.912
♪ ♪

794
01:05:32.127 --> 01:05:33.712
(groaning)

795
01:05:38.301 --> 01:05:40.428
(softly) No more.

796
01:05:40.511 --> 01:05:42.096
No more.

797
01:05:44.515 --> 01:05:46.600
(short breaths)

798
01:06:10.875 --> 01:06:11.584
My love.

799
01:06:11.667 --> 01:06:14.504
(breathing stops)

800
01:06:26.348 --> 01:06:29.352
♪ ♪

800
